==English==
===Suffix===
'''-ate'''
# as an adjective
## having the specified thing - e.g. lobate
## characterized by the specified thing - e.g. Italianate
## resembling the specified thing - e.g. palmate
# as a noun
## a thing characterised by the specified thing - e.g. apostate
## a [[rank]] or [[office]] - e.g. rabbinate
##{{chemistry}} a [[derivative]] of a specified [[element]] or [[compound]]; especially a [[salt]] or [[ester]] of an [[acid]] whose name ends in [[-ic]] - e.g. acetate
# as a verb
## to [[act]] in the specified manner - e.g. abbreviate
===Derived terms===
* very many (maybe later)